<h1>Group activities and team building in the Brecon Beacons National Park</h1>
<div class="article-video right clearfix"/>
<p/><p>
<span style="font-size:18px;">With masses of enthusiastic activity companies and plenty of accommodation suitable for groups, the Brecon Beacons is an exciting choice for a group getaway or team building trip.</span></p>
<p>
<img src="/website/var/tmp/thumb_2956__auto_450078387bf1c6122aa1db3e318c6c98.jpeg" style="width: 704px; height: 528px; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; float: right;"/>The Brecon Beacons National Park has masses to offer groups of students, families, friends, stag and hen parties and corporate groups.</p>
<p>You can book a regular activity session, or ask one of our experienced organisers to put together a special programme which could be a mixture of fun activities, physical challenges and problem-solving exercises. Your trip could be designed to develop management and leadership skills. Alternatively, it could simply be a fun occasion which will leave you all bonded and refreshed.</p>
<p>The most popular group activities include:</p>
<h2>Water activities</h2>
<p>Canoeing, kayaking, stand-up paddleboarding, whitewater rafting, raft building, sailing, windsurfing</p>
<h2>Walking and riding</h2>
<p>Hill walking, orienteering, geocaching, cycling, mountain biking, quad biking, horse riding, pony trekking</p>
<h2>Nature and skills building</h2>
<p>Navigation, bushcraft, wildlife-watching, archery, clay pigeon shooting</p>
<h2>Adventure activities</h2>
<p>Caving, rock climbing, abseiling, gorge walking, ropes and zip wires</p>
